The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Lanka pounds Tigers 

 Colombo, Feb. 6 (Reuters): Sri Lankan helicopter gunships fired rockets at Tamil Tigers in the islands far northeast today, the military said. There were no immediate word on casualties. 

 The attack in the northeastern district of Trincomalee comes just days after President Mahinda Rajapakse vowed to defeat and tame the Tigers while offering to resume peace talks. 

 Iran diplomat 

 Baghdad (Reuters): Gunmen kidnapped a senior Iranian diplomat in Baghdad, Iraqi and Iranian officials said on Tuesday, and Tehran blamed the US military and demanded his release. 

 DNA samples 

 Washington (PTI): The Bush administration has decided to collect DNA samples from suspects who have been arrested but not convicted and add to the national database, a proposal resented by privacy advocates. 




